      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Tapering down your medication, even if you feel healthy, isn't advisable without medical supervision. Warfarin's effectiveness and safety are closely monitored by your healthcare provider, who considers your specific health profile, including your diet, genetic factors, and other medications. A dosage too low could lead to clot formation, while a dosage too high remains unnecessary. Never self-adjust your medication; it's best to discuss your goals and concerns with your doctor. They can provide a safe and personalized plan. Your health and safety come first.",
      "source": "target",
